{"image_id": "ZBRA_2003_page_21", "image_size": [1650, 1275], "ocr": [{"text": "19", "bbox": [1558.9, 1216.6, 1577.2, 1233.2]}, {"text": "Z E B R A  T E C H N O L O G I E S  C O R P O R A T I O N", "bbox": [1192.3, 147.0, 1538.7, 157.4]}, {"text": "Departments of Revenue for Illinois and California related to research and experi-", "bbox": [111.9, 261.6, 773.7, 278.2]}, {"text": "mentation tax credits for 1998 to 2001. Because of the uncertainty of receiving", "bbox": [111.9, 290.7, 753.4, 307.4]}, {"text": "the credits, which require significant subjective analysis, we established a 100%", "bbox": [111.9, 319.9, 767.4, 336.5]}, {"text": "reserve against the contingent receivable for the refunds during each of the first", "bbox": [111.9, 349.0, 769.5, 365.7]}, {"text": "two quarters of 2003. In September 2003 the IRS approved our refund applications.", "bbox": [111.9, 378.2, 793.9, 394.9]}, {"text": "Because California and Illinois law mirror the Federal Tax Code, we now expect to", "bbox": [111.9, 407.4, 780.7, 424.0]}, {"text": "have those refunds approved as well.", "bbox": [111.9, 436.5, 420.3, 453.2]}, {"text": "For 2003, the effective income tax rate was 32.6% versus 35.4% for 2002. Excluding", "bbox": [111.9, 494.9, 794.4, 511.5]}, {"text": "the two tax adjustments discussed above, our effective tax rate would have been", "bbox": [111.9, 524.0, 777.1, 540.7]}, {"text": "35% for 2003. With the settlement of the Illinois tax dispute, we anticipate our tax", "bbox": [111.9, 553.2, 779.2, 569.9]}, {"text": "provision rate will be 34.75% beginning in the first quarter of 2004.", "bbox": [111.9, 582.4, 660.5, 599.0]}, {"text": "Net Income", "bbox": [111.9, 640.7, 205.7, 657.4]}, {"text": "Zebra’s net income is summarized below (in thousands, except per share amounts):", "bbox": [111.9, 669.9, 793.3, 686.6]}, {"text": "Three Months Ended", "bbox": [394.0, 717.4, 546.6, 732.0]}, {"text": "Year Ended", "bbox": [650.6, 717.4, 731.4, 732.0]}, {"text": "December 31,", "b